  "body": "I intentionally cause the rolling update to fail by specifying a non-existent image in the spec, so that it times out.\n\n```\nkubectl rolling-update copper -f iron.yml --update-period=1s --timeout=30s\nerror: timed out waiting for any update progress to be made\n\nCreated iron\nScaling up iron from 0 to 1, scaling down copper from 1 to 0 (keep 1 pods available, don't exceed 2 pods)\nScaling iron up to 1\n```\n\nrollback then fails with a timeout as well, despite the original replication controller having 1 healthy replica:\n\n```\nkubectl rolling-update copper -f iron.yml --update-period=1s --timeout=30s --rollback\nerror: timed out waiting for any update progress to be made\n\nSetting \"copper\" replicas to 1\nContinuing update with existing controller copper.\nScaling up copper from 1 to 1, scaling down iron from 1 to 0 (keep 1 pods available, don't exceed 2 pods)\n```\n\nThis is on 1.1.2. I expect the rollback to succeed as the original rc (copper) has 1 healthy replica still.\n",
